text: Wilhelmshaven is a coastal town in Lower Saxony, Germany. It is on the western side of the Jade Bight, a bay of the North Sea. It is Germany's main military port. ==Twin towns â€“ Sister cities== Wilhelmshaven is twinned with: * Vichy, France (since 1965) * Norfolk, Virginia, U.S. (since 1976) * Dunfermline, Fife, Scotland, (since 1979) * Qingdao, China (since 1992) * Bad Harzburg, Germany (since 1988) * Bydgoszcz, Poland (since 2006) ==References== ==Other websites== Category:Towns in Lower Saxony
